  "body": "Output of `helm version`:\r\n\r\n```\r\nversion.BuildInfo{Version:\"v3.0.0-alpha.1\", GitCommit:\"b9a54967f838723fe241172a6b94d18caf8bcdca\", GitTreeState:\"clean\"}\r\n```\r\n\r\nExample issue (note escaping of `$` is for the shell):\r\n\r\n```\r\nexport PATH=\"$HOME/bin/helm-v3.0.0-alpha.1-darwin-amd64:$PATH\"\r\ncd /tmp\r\nrm -rf colon-missing\r\nhelm create colon-missing\r\ncat >colon-missing/templates/deployment.yaml <<EOF\r\n{{ \\$someEmptyValue := \"\" }}\r\n{{ \\$myvar := \"abc\" }}\r\n{{- required (printf \"%s: something is missing\" \\$myvar) \\$someEmptyValue | repeat 0 }}\r\nEOF\r\nhelm template myrelease colon-missing/\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis will fail with a truncated error message:\r\n\r\n```\r\nError: render error at (colon-missing/templates/deployment.yaml:3:4): something is missing\r\n```\r\n\r\nOnce you remove the `:` from the custom error message (`printf \"%s <colon removed here> something is missing\" $myvar`), the error output is as expected:\r\n\r\n```\r\nError: render error at (colon-missing/templates/deployment.yaml:3:4): abc <colon removed here> something is missing\r\n```",
